Completed Questions
========================================

Similar to Ongoing questions, but non-editable.

====================

Ongoing questions

(if there's more than one question taking place, show a menu)

Then, for each question,

We need to fit:

   Link to menu (<all questions>)

   (upper-left col)Question (a summarized version, when clicked, it gets loaded in idea viewer) --invite more friends link gets shown to question owner, shows a popup form. Also "edit question" is available before participation starts. 

   (left col) Idea summaries - when clicked, idea is selected and loaded in the idea viewer

   (right col)Idea viewer shows ideas, accepts per-idea comments, a-la-facebook.

   

================

After submitting a new question, a message will appear:

Your question is created. We have sent an email invitation to each of your friends.
	
You can invite more friends with the "invite more friends" link in your question's page. 

You can also make changes to your question's settings before participation starts.

You can now <go to your question's page> or <create another question>.

A direct link to your question is: htttp://fdasdasd.


HOW TO IMPLEMENT:

   Each invitation goes to a table keyed by question_id and email, with a generated invitation_id. Invitation text contains a link with the invitation_id.

When sending invitations, we do:

   With question id, email, look for a record in Invitation table.
   If there is, reuse invitation_id.
   Else create new record.
   Send invitation.



When arriving with invitation id...
  Wait for user to log in to FB.
  Send FB-id, invitation id back to server.

  Look up email, question id in invitation table.

  Create User if needed. Update email address of user.

  Create Question-User if not already there.

  Return question_id, question data, remaining votes to client.





===============


<p>
En email invitation will be sent to participants. Then, after logging-in with their facebook accounts, they will be assigned an alias, and immediately they will be able to provide and discuss answers under this alias. They can submit answers until the last date for answers, and after that they will be able to cast 10 votes for the best answers.
</p>

<p>
The rules of the system are:
</p>

<ul>
<li>users participate under an alias</li>

<li>users can vote only after the last date for answers</li>

<li>vote counts are shown only after voting is closed</li>

<li>votes are kept secret (no one is informed of who voted for what)</li>

<li>real identities are revealed at the end (so that the authors of the answers can be known)</li>

<li>participants can invite others to participate</li>

<li>question is open for public view, but only invited friends can participate</li>

<p>These rules can be changed using the advanced-view questionnaire.</p>





and they will immediately be able to enter answers and discuss them.

participating

